#Text=Wikinews interviews Indiana State Senator Mike Delph
#Text=Saturday , March 29 , 2014
#Text=This is an edited transcript of a Wikinews exclusive audio interview .
#Text=File : Senator Mike Delph 2014 . jpg
#Text=Indiana State Senator Mike Delph , S-29 ( Image missing from commons : image ; log )
#Text=On Wikinews , we have an exclusive audio interview with Indiana State Senator Mike Delph .
#Text=Today is Thursday , March 27 , 2014 .
#Text=I am Chad Tew and we are here in The Edge radio studios with my journalism students and recording from the campus of the University of Southern Indiana .
#Text=This is Wikinews .
#Text=Introduction
#Text=Indiana State Senator Mike Delph is a Republican who represents the northwest side of Indianapolis and Carmel , as well as Zionsville , Indiana .
#Text=After being selected to finish former State Senator J. Murray Clark 's final term in 2005 , Mike Delph has served two full terms for District 29 in the Indiana State Senate .
#Text=He is currently facing re-election this fall .
#Text=His opponent is likely to be Democrat JD Ford , who is running as an openly gay candidate .

#Text=Senator Delph has also been considered in the past for US Congress but he declined to run , and he has already been mentioned in the Indiana media as a possible candidate for any potential opening in the US Senate in 2016 .
#Text=He is widely known across the state of Indiana for both his Arizona-style legislation on immigration and his support of traditional marriage .
#Text=During the legislative session this year , Senator Delph made what is known in Indiana as the " tweet heard around the world " .
#Text=The tweet announced the defeat of a proposed amendment to the Indiana State Constitution in a form that would have banned civil unions .
#Text=Senate leader David Long punished Delph because of this tweet on the grounds that it concerned confidential caucus information .
#Text=What exactly took place in that Republican caucus and between Senator Delph and Senator Long is currently unknown to the public .
#Text=Tew :
#Text=State Senator Delph
#Text=good morning and welcome to Wikinews .
#Text=Thanks for having me professor .
#Text=Interview ( part I ) : A biographical portrait
#Text=Chad Tew : Here with our first question is Ashely Jones Phillips .
#Text=Jones Phillips : Hi !
#Text=Good morning , Senator Mike Delph .
#Text=My name Is Ashley Jones-Phillips .
#Text=The first question that I have is , I wanted to know if you can tell me a little bit about your parents , where are you from , and where were you were raised and born ?
#Text=Sure , I grew up here in Carmel , Indiana .
#Text=I was raised by my mother .
#Text=My parents were divorced for most of my upbringing .

#Text=While my father was on leave from his business — or actually helping his dad , my grandfather , with one of their plants out east — I was born in South Weymouth , Massachusetts , just outside of Boston .
#Text=So I was actually born in Boston or just outside of Boston but raised in Indiana by my mother .
#Text=I have three brothers .
#Text=I shared a bedroom with my little brother John .
#Text=And my two older brothers Jamie and Stephen were with us as well .
